## What
Fixes two empty catch blocks in `src/mdns.js` that were silently ignoring errors.

## Changes
```js
// Line 166 - Before
try { instance.destroy(); } catch (e) {}

// Line 166 - After
try { instance.destroy(); } catch (e) {
  console.error('[mdns] Failed to destroy instance:', e);
}

// Line 240 - Before
} catch (e) {}

// Line 240 - After
} catch (e) {
  console.error('[mdns] Failed to remove listener or destroy instance:', e);
}
```

## Why
Silent catch blocks hide real issues. Logging the errors makes debugging easier without changing any behavior.

Closes #41
